  "prompt": "How fast can helicopters travel?",
  "response": "The speed of a helicopter can vary significantly depending on its design, size, and purpose. Generally, helicopters have a cruising speed ranging between 100 to 150 knots (115 to 170 miles per hour or 185 to 275 kilometers per hour). Some high-performance military helicopters, like the Sikorsky S-97 Raider, can reach speeds up to 220 knots (253 miles per hour or 407 kilometers per hour). However, typical civilian helicopters usually operate within the lower range of speeds.",
